The Rhett and Link SHIPface Challenge!

1) Take the pictures from our TUMBLR. (http://rhettandlink.tumblr.com/tagged/SHIPfaceChallenge) or any pictures you can find.
2) Download the pictures and manipulate them to "Shipface" us. This means you can switch up our eyes, our noses, hair, beard, anything! Just mash our faces together in a cool/silly way.
3)Post the photo to TUMBLR with the hashtag #Shipface #rhink
4) We'll find the best ones and re-blog them for everyone to see!! Now you will have contributed to the rise of Shipfacing!

Nesquik® Girl Scouts® Thin Mints® and Nesquik® Girl Scouts® Caramel Coconut flavors are available now for a limited time, so grab ‘em while you can!
 
The Contest begins on September 8, 2014 at 12:00 a.m. Eastern Time ("ET"), ends on October 12, 2014 at 11:59 p.m. ET (the "Contest Period"),
 
How to Enter:
1.       "Follow" @NestleNesquik on Twitter; and
2.       Tweet a photo of yourself enjoying a "Double Awesome" moment and include the hashtag #DblAwesomeContest (herein, your "Submission") in order to receive one (1) Contest entry into the applicable Weekly Contest Period. A Double Awesome moment is one in which you enjoy a bottle of NESQUIK® Girl Scout CookieTM flavored milk while doing something almost as awesome and unique as the drink itself.
 
Prizes:
ONE (1) GRAND PRIZE: Winner will have a choice between one (1) of the following four (4) trip options:
1.       A ski trip for two (2) to Salt Lake City, Utah.
2.       A trip for two (2) to New York City, New York.
3.       A trip for two (2) to Myrtle Beach, SC.
4.       A trip for two (2) to Orlando, FL
 
FINALIST PRIZES (One (1) per Weekly Contest Period): Two (2) months’ supply of 14 oz. Ready-to-Drink NESQUIK® Girl Scout CookieTM Flavored milk awarded as four (4) cases, totaling forty-eight (48) bottles per finalist. ARV: $96 per finalist. Prizes are non-transferable and no substitution will be made except as provided herein at the Sponsor’s sole discretion. Sponsor reserves the right to substitute a prize for one of equal or greater value if the designated prize should become unavailable for any reason. Winners are responsible for all taxes and fees associated with prize receipt and/or use. Limit: One (1) Finalist prize per person.
 
NO PURCHASE NECESSARY. Legal residents of the 50 United States (D.C.), 18 years or older who did not purchase any equipment for purposes of entering the Contest. Enter Contest by: 10/12/14. To enter and for Official Rules, including prize descriptions, visit ‪http://bit.ly/1tucsbX . Void where prohibited.
 Girl Scouts of the USATM
